  "rules": [
    "[P1] Calculate date intervals precisely using year, month, and day differences",
    "[P1] Explicitly search all relevant sources for required procedures, orders, measurements, device status, immunization records, lab values, items, or observations within each specified time window before concluding absence or performing calculations",
    "[P1] Enumerate all possible medication formulations, aliases, and alternate spellings (including generic/brand names) when searching active orders",
    "[P1] Confirm device or item presence and placement duration before action",
    "[P1] Always verify system state post-action to ensure desired outcome",
    "[P1] Check date of last required intervention before acting",
    "[P1] Order repeat intervention if interval since last exceeds protocol threshold",
    "[P1] Always verify procedure timing against the required threshold before skipping actions",
    "[P1] Verify completeness of data before reporting summary statistics",
    "[P1] Only initiate new or repeat actions when triggering criteria are met and required intervals verified",
    "[P1] Verify absence of removal or modification order before initiating removal or modification",
    "[P1] Ensure exactly one active order by discontinuing duplicates and confirm completion",
    "[P1] Avoid unnecessary actions when triggering items are absent",
    "[P1] Execute required actions, not just describe workflow",
    "[P1] Match every active order requiring a co-prescription with its required pair and initiate when missing after verification"
  ],
